Description: 1989 Gretsch 6121 Roundup Orange Chambered-Body El. Guitar w/Case #8910121-40 Up for sale a 1989 Gretsch 6121 Roundup Orange Chambered-Body Electric Guitar w/Case - #8910121-40!  This instrument is a Used Model in Excellent Cosmetic Condition and in Perfect Playing Condition.  On this one, there are some scratches, marks on the underside (gold-finish) of the pickguard (see 1st and 9th pictures), there is a tiny paint chip on the headstock (see 24th picture) and there are some scratches, marks, dents, few tiny notches, a light deterioration of the metal parts (gold-plated) and other signs of wear here and there (see 13th to 24th pictures), but really nothing major.  Unit comes with its Gretsch Hardshell Case. GRETSCH ROUNDUP 6121The modern-era take on the classic 6121 Chet Atkins Solidbody, borrowing the vintage 6130 Roundup's model name, the 6121 Roundup was offered from 1989 until about 2007, when Chet Atkins came back into the fold. The rebirth years : 1988-2002, The Fender years : 2003-present.Block inlays of cactuses, rifles, arrows and steer heads mosey up the laminated neck, drifting towards the horseshoe-inlaid headpiece. The mahogany body with the western maple top is mounted with a 24K gold-plated Gretsch Bigsby tailpiece, and, right on top, emblazoned with the searing "G" Brand.
